monstrating how the director's radical approaches to narrative, editing, sound and shot composition have made the cinema into an analytical tool in its own right.The book will be essential to all students of Godard's films, and of interest to scholars of modern and contemporary French cinema, culture and thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aA bout de soufflé.  aCahiers du cinema.  aFrench film studies.  aJean-Luc Godard.  aMasculin feminine.  aadvertising.  aanglophone film studies.  aapocryphal stories.  acapitalism.  acinematic homage.  agreat film directors.  aliterary sensibility.  amusic videos.  atelevision.1 aMorrey, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614155240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141552423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141552/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles